    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.34-38_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">34</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Key Stone
                        <hi rend="caps">S</hi> Dak
                        Nov 5, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Kola John</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Got your letter a little late as I have been gone for a while and I think that is a good Idea but I dont know how to do it. Do you want me in person.? I could come if its worth it, in person. Or do you want <del>to</del> just my voice. I have a recording machine of my own. I could do it my self<sic>myself</sic>, but I dont know how long it takes you to do this, is it the whole work or part of it if I know I can sure <del>dot</del> do it</p>
                
                <p>But I thought to appear in other <hi rend="caps">TV</hi> I might be able
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.34-38_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">35</fw>
                
                    <unclear/> <unclear>a</unclear>ppear in person.</p>
                
                <p>I will approch<sic>apporach</sic> the <hi rend="caps">TV</hi> outfit and have a talk with them may be that can be worked out</p>
                
                <p>But <add>if</add> your management thinks I'll appear in person. that can be done</p>
                
                <p>If that could be done I can come right away and take my time coming back.</p>
                
                <p>May be I can earn something coming back as I do lectures on my father's books.</p>
                
                <p>We are both fine Mrs. Black Elk &amp; I. <unclear>Give</unclear> our best to all We too always think of you all.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Meta Kola</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Benjamin Black Elk</signed>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Key Stone</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">SD</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.34-38_0003"/>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener>
                    <p>May be you can call me my no is
                        <lb/>
                        2284
                            <lb/>
                            Key Stone
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="caps">SD</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    after 6 at evening</p>
                </postscript>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.34-38_0004"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">36</fw>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S-</hi></opener>
                    <p>Oh yes John. I forgot something very important</p>
                    
                    <p>At <del><unclear>my</unclear></del> Manderson. they are building a meeting house in Memory of Black Elk my father</p>
                    
                    <p>This will be a good living memorial to our father better than a <hi rend="underline">tom<sic>tomb</sic></hi> stone</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="enclosure">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.34-38_0005"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">37</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    St. Agnes Mission
                    Manderson, <hi rend="caps">S. D.</hi>
                </opener>
                <p><hi rend="underline">Subject Matter:</hi> Renewal of the crumbling meeting house of St. Agnes.</p>
                
                <p>Whereas the present meeting house has stood for half a century, and whereas it is now crumbling and rotting away,</p>
                
                <p>And whereas it is the most used gathering place in the area, being used for socials, local district meetings of the council, Indian and government meetings and sundry other projects, and has been so used for all the years,</p>
                
                <p>And whereas we, the officers of the St. Joseph's Society and the St. Mary's Society in union with the whole membership of St. Agnes are desirous that out meeting house still be so used for community gatherings,</p>
                
                <p>And whereas we cherish the memory of the late Catechist, Mr. Nicholas Black Elk whose work is in great part the reason for many of us being of the Faith today,</p>
                
                <p>Be it resolved in our mi<del>s</del><add>d</add>s't here assembled,
                    <list>
                        <item>1. That a new structure be established here to replace the jaunty log cabin now near rotte<del>e</del><add>d</add> away,</item>
                
                        <item>2. And that said new meeting hall be dedicated after God, to the memory of Mr. Nicholas Black Elk as a token of appreciation for his work here, and as a monument to his memory.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                
                <p>Be it further resolved that all money gathered for the above purpose, be deposited with our Pastor, presently <add>Rev. Daniel, Tanitre, <hi rend="caps">S.J.</hi></add> <del>Father Price, <hi rend="caps">S.J.</hi></del> of Holy Rosary Mission, Pine Ridge South Dakota.</p>
                
                <p>The above has the approval of all: whereunto the following signatures are set:</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Pastor: Father Price S.J.</signed>
                    
                    Societies: St. Joseph's
                    <signed>Pres. Tom Black Bear</signed>
                    <signed><hi rend="caps">V.</hi> Pres. Moses Runs Against</signed>
                    <signed>Treas. Laururee Hollow Horn</signed>
                    
                    St. Mary's
                    <signed>Pres. Emma Hollow Horn</signed>
                    <signed><hi rend="caps">V.</hi> Pres. Grace Hollow Horn</signed>
                    <signed>Trea. <unclear>Lula Tess</unclear> Bonnet</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">
                    <hi rend="underline">Send all contributions to</hi>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Rev Daniel Tanitre <hi rend="caps">S.J.</hi></addrLine>
                            <addrLine>St Agnes Mission</addrLine>
                                <addrLine>Manderson</addrLine>
                                    <addrLine><hi rend="caps">SD</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                </note>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.34-38_0006"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">38</fw>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <hi rend="caps">AFTER 5 DAYS RETURN TO</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Ben Black Elk
                    Keystone
                    <hi rend="caps">SD</hi>
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    KEYSTONE,
                    NOV 5
                    5-PM
                    1958
                    S.DAK.
                </ab>
